<paragraph id="8BEC369DFFD0D117FF6FFA27FE4003CB" blockId="2.[151,509,1462,1488]" box="[151,509,1462,1488]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<heading id="D0A481F1FFD0D117FF6FFA27FE4003CB" bold="true" box="[151,509,1462,1488]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B927EA8FFFD0D117FF6FFA27FE4003CB" bold="true" box="[151,509,1462,1488]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D1EFFD0D117FF16FA27FE4003CB" authority="Schmitz, 1944" authorityName="Schmitz" authorityYear="1944" box="[238,509,1462,1488]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Billotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B927EA8FFFD0D117FF16FA27FEF503CB" bold="true" box="[238,328,1462,1488]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Billotia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B6CFFD0D117FEB7FA27FE4003CB" author="Schmitz" box="[335,509,1462,1488]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" refString="Schmitz, H. (1944) Billotia inermis, eine neue Gattung und Art der europaeischen Phoriden (Diptera). Natuurhistorisch Maandblad, 33 (7 - 8), 50 - 52." type="journal article" year="1944">
Schmitz, 
<number id="3D9B24BAFFD0D117FE3AFA27FE4003CB" box="[450,509,1462,1488]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" value="1944.0">1944</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC369DFFD0D117FF6FFA66FAA40066" blockId="2.[151,1436,1527,1661]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
The genus had long been known from a single Central European species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D1EFFD0D117FC21FA68FB46000B" authority="Schmitz, 1944" authorityName="Schmitz" authorityYear="1944" box="[985,1275,1527,1552]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Billotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inermis">
<emphasis id="B927EA8FFFD0D117FC21FA68FBF3000B" box="[985,1102,1529,1552]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">B. inermis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B6CFFD0D117FBADFA66FB46000B" author="Schmitz" box="[1109,1275,1527,1552]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" refString="Schmitz, H. (1944) Billotia inermis, eine neue Gattung und Art der europaeischen Phoriden (Diptera). Natuurhistorisch Maandblad, 33 (7 - 8), 50 - 52." type="journal article" year="1944">
Schmitz, 
<number id="3D9B24BAFFD0D117FB38FA69FB46000B" box="[1216,1275,1528,1552]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" value="1944.0">1944</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, until 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D1EFFD0D117FABAFA68FA21000B" box="[1346,1436,1529,1552]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Billotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papii">
<emphasis id="B927EA8FFFD0D117FABAFA68FA21000B" box="[1346,1436,1529,1552]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">B. papii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from Tuscany (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B6CFFD0D117FE05F98DFD3F002F" author="Gori" box="[509,642,1564,1589]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" refString="Gori, M. (2000) Due nuove specie di foridi italiani: Billotia papii n. sp. e Triphleba ausoniae n. sp. (Diptera Phoridae). Bollettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 132 (2), 175 - 180." type="journal article" year="2000">
Gori, 
<number id="3D9B24BAFFD0D117FDBDF98DFD3F002F" box="[581,642,1564,1588]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" value="2000.0">2000</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Whereas the former is known from both males and females, the description of the latter is based on female only. This makes confident attribution of specimens to hand difficult until males are available from the 
<typeStatus id="54E8883FFFD0D117FDEEF9F4FDFB0066" box="[534,582,1637,1661]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D1EFFD0D117FD3EF9F4FCA20067" box="[710,799,1637,1660]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Billotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papii">
<emphasis id="B927EA8FFFD0D117FD3EF9F4FCA20067" box="[710,799,1637,1660]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">B. papii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, or females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D1EFFD0D117FC3FF9F5FBA60066" box="[967,1051,1636,1661]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Billotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B927EA8FFFD0D117FC3FF9F5FBA60066" box="[967,1051,1636,1661]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Billotia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are procured in 
<collectingCountry id="F344760DFFD0D117FB2BF9F5FAA80066" box="[1235,1301,1636,1661]" name="Israel" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Israel</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
